      "blocks": {
        "origin-eyebrow": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "The Beginning",
            "size": "sm",
            "uppercase": true,
            "muted": true
          }
        },
        "origin-heading": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Born From a Simple Idea",
            "size": "4xl"
          }
        },
        "origin-text": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Corkwell started with a frustration: every wine bar in the neighborhood was either too precious or too loud. Nick Alvarez and Reena Chandra wanted something in between — a place where you could learn about natural wine without a lecture, or just order a glass of whatever's good without overthinking it.</p><p>They found a former speakeasy basement with exposed brick and a vaulted ceiling, stripped it to the bones, and filled it with 200 bottles they'd personally tasted. Corkwell opened in 2019 and hasn't had an empty Friday since.</p>",
            "size": "base",
            "uppercase": false,
            "muted": false
          }
        }
      },
      "blocksOrder": ["origin-eyebrow", "origin-heading", "origin-text"]
    },
    "philosophy": {
      "type": "split-content",
      "settings": {
        "balance": "equal",
        "sticky_column": "none",
        "color_scheme": "standard-accent"
      },
      "blocks": {
        "phil-heading": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Our Approach to Wine",
            "size": "4xl",
            "position": "left"
          }
        },
        "phil-text": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>We believe the best wine is the wine you enjoy. Our job is to help you find it — whether that's a $12 glass of Côtes du Rhône or a $200 bottle of aged Barolo.</p>",
            "size": "base",
            "uppercase": false,
            "muted": false,
            "position": "left"
          }
        },
        "phil-features-1": {
          "type": "features",
          "settings": {
            "features": "+ Small producers over big brands\n+ Sustainable and organic when possible\n+ Every bottle tasted before it's listed",
            "position": "right"
          }
        },
        "phil-features-2": {
          "type": "features",
          "settings": {
            "features": "+ Staff trained, never scripted\n+ Rotating by-the-glass selection weekly\n+ No corking fees — bring your own for $15",
            "position": "right"
          }
        }
      },
      "blocksOrder": ["phil-heading", "phil-text", "phil-features-1", "phil-features-2"]
